OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FA recovery truck driver accused of
OL,8,Fmurdering his teenage girlfriend by
OL,9,Fcrushing her against a lamppost has
OL,10,Ftold a jury he lied about a hit-and-
OL,11,Frun because he "panicked".
OL,13,FProsecutors allege 19-year-old Lily
OL,14,FWhitehouse suffered catastrophic chest
OL,15,Finjuries when Mohammed Azim used his
OL,16,Fflatbed truck "as a weapon" to pin her
OL,17,Fto a lamppost during an argument in
OL,18,FOldbury on his 41st birthday on 5
OL,19,FNovember last year.
OL,26,@sD@POUsD@YO]xD@OOUxD@[O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34402
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FMr Azim, who is on trial at
OL,8,FWolverhampton Crown Court, denies
OL,9,Fmurder, telling a jury on Monday he
OL,10,Fhit her accidentally after dropping
OL,11,Fher off near her home, after initially
OL,12,Ftelling police another vehicle had hit
OL,13,Fher and driven off.
OL,15,FProsecution counsel Rachel Brand KC
OL,16,Ftold Azim, who cried in the witness
OL,17,Fbox and dabbed his eyes with a tissue,
OL,18,Fthat he had lied repeatedly about how
OL,19,FMs Whitehouse, a mother to a newborn
OL,20,Fbaby fathered by another man, came by
OL,21,Fher death.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G2/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34403
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FThe court heard he told police and
OL,8,Fparamedics he had seen Ms Whitehouse
OL,9,Fget hit by a car that had driven off
OL,10,Fand left the scene, a story they found
OL,11,F"strange", but he told his trial he
OL,12,Fhad accidentally run her over as he
OL,13,Ftried to leave her and go home.
OL,15,F"You were angry with her that night
OL,16,Fand you chased her down the road in
OL,17,Fyour truck, didn't you?" Ms Brand
OL,18,Fasked the defendant.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@IO]wD@AOUyD@XO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G3/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FHe said, "No that's 100% not true,
OL,8,Fthere was no need for me to chase
OL,9,Fher... when I was about to leave, she
OL,10,Fwanted to come back with me, that's
OL,11,Fthe truth."
OL,13,FMs Brand said the defendant told the
OL,14,F999 call handler he had seen her hit
OL,15,Fby a car because he was trying to
OL,16,Fprotect himself.
OL,26,@oD@JOUsD@KO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G4/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,F"When you told that lie, you were
OL,8,Fthinking of yourself weren't you,
OL,9,Fbecause you didn't want to get the
OL,10,Fblame," Ms Brand said during cross-
OL,11,Fexamination.
OL,13,FThe defendant replied, "I didn't
OL,14,Fbelieve myself that this had happened.
OL,15,FI was lost, my head was all over the
OL,16,Fplace."
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@GO]uD@XOUxD@GO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FMs Brand added, "You kept up these
OL,8,Flies when paramedics and police
OL,9,Farrived, you told them it happened
OL,10,Fdown there, you pointed at an SUV type
OL,11,Fvehicle and said it was like that one.
OL,13,F"You said 'I wish I could have chased
OL,14,Fhim', didn't you? You also said 'That
OL,15,Fmotherf*****, if I could catch him I
OL,16,Fwould kill him', didn't you?"
OL,18,FAccepting he had said that, Azim said,
OL,19,F"I wasn't in control myself, I was
OL,20,Ftotally lost."
OL,26,@oD@QOUuD@AOUxD@]O]{D@AOU|D@NO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FThe prosecutor said Azim had also lied
OL,8,Frepeatedly to doctors who had visited
OL,9,Fhim while he was in custody, including
OL,10,Fsaying he did not have a romantic
OL,11,Frelationship with the victim, that he
OL,12,Fcould not speak to one professional
OL,13,Fbecause there was no Mirpuri
OL,14,Finterpreter, and that he could not
OL,15,Fhave dropped Ms Whitehouse off at her
OL,16,Fhome in Amber Drive on the night of
OL,17,Fthe incident because there were "drugs
OL,18,Fpeople after her".
OL,26,@yD@aOUzD@QO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G7/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FAzim said he could not remember saying
OL,8,Fthese things because he has been on
OL,9,Fmedication.
OL,11,FMs Brand said: "Your main thought has
OL,12,Fbeen to pretend it wasn't your fault,
OL,13,Fisn't it?"
OL,15,FThe defendant replied: "No... it
OL,16,Fdidn't feel real to me, my head was
OL,17,Fall over the place, I panicked."
OL,26,@sD@POUuD@JO]wD@XOUyD@`O]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G8/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FAsked why he told police after his
OL,8,Farrest that he could not remember what
OL,9,Fhad happened to Ms Whitehouse, Azim
OL,10,Fsaid: "I wasn't in my control, I was
OL,11,Flost, I panicked.
OL,13,F"It was shocking, it was a shock."
OL,15,FMs Brand asked, "Didn't you want to
OL,16,Ftell the police it had been a terrible
OL,17,Faccident?"
OL,19,FThe defendant said, "It took me a long
OL,20,Ftime to recover from this trauma, I
OL,21,Fwas lost."
OL,26,@uD@AOUuD@bO]wD@QOUyD@JO]{D@UOU}D@JO]
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G9/11
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BC Eng News CThis Day FReg TV
FL,345,340,120,260,000,100
PN,34410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F344A1781765277
OL,3,CMan accused of girlfriend's murder
OL,4,Ctells court he 'panicked' and lied to
OL,5,Cpolice
OL,7,FWiping his eyes with a tissue as he
OL,8,Fwas asked by his defence barrister,
OL,9,FImran Shafi KC, how his mental state
OL,10,Fwas, Azim said he is no longer under
OL,11,Fobservation due to concerns he may
OL,12,Ftake his own life, but was still on
OL,13,Fmedication.
OL,15,FHe said, "If I could give my life to
OL,16,Fbring her back, I would."
OL,18,FThe trial continues.
OL,26,@wD@JOUxD@YO]
